anced-thrust rocket,\u003csup class=\\\"reference\\\" id=\\\"cite_ref-sn20150508_108-0\\\"\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"#cite_note-sn20150508-108\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e[\u003c/span\u003e101\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e]\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/sup\u003e but the change to the maiden flight position was announced in October 2015.\u003csup class=\\\"reference\\\" id=\\\"cite_ref-sn20151016_107-1\\\"\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"#cite_note-sn20151016-107\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e[\u003c/span\u003e100\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e]\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/sup\u003e SpaceX received a permit from the \u003ca class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" href=\\\"/wiki/FAA\\\" title=\\\"FAA\\\"\u003eFAA\u003c/a\u003e to land the booster \u003ca href=\\\"/wiki/Landing_Zones_1_and_2\\\" title=\\\"Landing Zones 1 and 2\\\"\u003eon solid ground\u003c/a\u003e at \u003ca href=\\\"/wiki/Cape_Canaveral_Space_Force_Station\\\" title=\\\"Cape Canaveral Space Force Station\\\"\u003eCape Canaveral\u003c/a\u003e\u003csup class=\\\"reference\\\" id=\\\"cite_ref-109\\\"\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"#cite_note-109\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e[\u003c/span\u003e102\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e]\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/sup\u003e and succeeded for the first time.\u003csup class=\\\"reference\\\" id=\\\"cite_ref-flight20-landing_106-1\\\"\u003e\u003ca href=\\\"#cite_note-flight20-landing-106\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e[\u003c/span\u003e99\u003cspan class=\\\"cite-bracket\\\"\u003e]\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/sup\u003e This booster, serial number \u003ca class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" href=\\\"/wiki/B1019\\\" title=\\\"B1019\\\"\u003eB1019\u003c/a\u003e, is now on permanent display outside SpaceX's headquarters in \u003ca href=\\\"/wiki/Hawthorne,_California\\\" title=\\\"Hawthorne, California\\\"\u003eHawthorne, California\u003c/a\u003e, at the in