\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026lt;td class=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003etable-success\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e style=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003ebackground: #9EFF9E; color:black; vertical-align: middle; text-align: center;\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;Success\u0026lt;sup class=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003ereference\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e id=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003ecite_ref-flight20-landing_106-0\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e#cite_note-flight20-landing-106\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003ecite-bracket\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;99\u0026lt;span class=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003ecite-bracket\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt;\u0026lt;br/\u0026gt;\u0026lt;small\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003enowrap\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;(ground pad)\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/small\u0026gt;\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/tr\u0026gt;\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u003cspan class=\"pl-s\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026lt;tr\u0026gt;\u003cspan class=\"pl-cce\"\u003e\\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"pl-pds\"\u003e\u0026quot;\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e,","      \u0026quot;\u0026lt;td colspan=\\\u0026quot;9\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;Payload included eleven satellites weighing 172 kg (379 lb) each,\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-gunter-og2_30-2\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-gunter-og2-30\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;24\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt; and a 142 kg (313 lb) mass simulator.\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-gunter-og2-sim_59-1\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-gunter-og2-sim-59\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;52\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt; First launch of the upgraded v1.1 version, with a 30% power increase.\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-sn20151016_107-0\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-sn20151016-107\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;100\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt; Orbcomm had originally agreed to be the third flight of the enhanced-thrust rocket,\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-sn20150508_108-0\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-sn20150508-108\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;101\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt; but the change to the maiden flight position was announced in October 2015.\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-sn20151016_107-1\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-sn20151016-107\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;100\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt; SpaceX received a permit from the \u0026lt;a class=\\\u0026quot;mw-redirect\\\u0026quot; href=\\\u0026quot;/wiki/FAA\\\u0026quot; title=\\\u0026quot;FAA\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;FAA\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt; to land the booster \u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;/wiki/Landing_Zones_1_and_2\\\u0026quot; title=\\\u0026quot;Landing Zones 1 and 2\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;on solid ground\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt; at \u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;/wiki/Cape_Canaveral_Space_Force_Station\\\u0026quot; title=\\\u0026quot;Cape Canaveral Space Force Station\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;Cape Canaveral\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-109\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-109\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;[\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;102\u0026lt;span class=\\\u0026quot;cite-bracket\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;]\u0026lt;/span\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/a\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/sup\u0026gt; and succeeded for the first time.\u0026lt;sup class=\\\u0026quot;reference\\\u0026quot; id=\\\u0026quot;cite_ref-flight20-landing_106-1\\\u0026quot;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;a href=\\\u0026quot;#cite_note-flight20-landing-106\\\u0026quot;\u0026g